{"build_type":"library","description":"The fertility gate as a self-contained helper so the reconcile orchestrator stays small (a giant orchestrator function miscompiles). Reads the manifest: if it carries skip_fertility (scratch runs do) returns 0 immediately so it does not recurse. Otherwise builds a fresh scratch base root slash dot fert slash genN, runs the just-built generation reconcile twice there (stage2 then stage3) via verify-generation-reproduces-toolchain-fixpoint, and returns 0 if the toolchain reproduces itself byte-identically. On sterile it emits the fertility-gate error and returns the nonzero verdict so the orchestrator skips the flip.","module_name":"verify-fertility-before-promoting-generation","package_name":"verify-fertility-before-promoting-generation","function_definitions":{"verify-fertility-before-promoting-generation":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"manifest_path","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"gen_bin_dir","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"root_dir","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"gen_n_str","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_skip","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"skip_fertility"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_fert","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":".fert"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_recon","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"reconcile"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_status","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"status"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_error","variable_type":"str","assignment_o